Crawley talking of saving and how to decide what you spend on. #hsfreport
Crawley speaking to Flexible Path and what "causes... [it] to make sense." #hsfreport
Crawley saying how much they tracked the responses and how important it was to listen to the public. #hsfreport
Tweeting, Facebook, HSF website, and document availability leveraged to hopefully set a new standard. #hsfreport
Augustine - this cmte was extremely different, "We tried very hard to make this a public engagement." #hsfreport
Questions with regard to public engagement. How was this committee different? #hsfreport
Augustine discussing needing to know the budget before you can answer that question. Preservation of knowledgebase brought up. #hsfreport
Question of workforce - "What time of reduction to the workforce do you recommend?" #hsfreport
Summary Report was provided at the end of August with a briefing to the White House. "They had the data they needed..." #hsfreport
Safety and accountability now being discussed #hsfreport
The options were crafted to address those issues. #hsfreport
"It's important to design a program that does that." A program that engages the public, commercialization., technology investment #hsfreport
Crawley thinks it's an excellent question. Describing how measurements were made. #hsfreport
Augustine talking of lunar landing, how it happened during the Vietnam War. The intangibles are immeasurable but powerful. #hsfreport
Reporter asking a question about "proving to the public" that funding is needed for NASA funding and how it will be addressed. #hsfreport
Augustine asked about submission of the report. White House and NASA has it. Additional support is possible, would be informal. #hsfreport
Augustine said Administrator needs to be able to make the workforce larger or smaller as needed. #hsfreport
Augustine saying NASA needs assurances to budget. Congressional and White House latitude needed to tailor the workforce. #hsfreport
Augustine speaking of studies, only time will tell concerning the impact of this study. #hsfreport
Augustine - NASA "had it right" the first time, problem is with budget assumptions. 2/3 of the budget NASA planned to see. #hsfreport
Crawley, "by the time you come out of all the analysis" $5B coming out for NASA's portion of the dev of the system. #hsfreport
Crawley speaking of low-earth orbit and a simple system to do the job. Space tourism, international customers, other uses. #hsfreport
Crawley talking of constraints placed on Ares I because of economics. Now speaking to alternatives. #hsfreport
Committee member Ed Crawley saying Ares I is really a matter of money. Budgetary environment has changed. #hsfreport
Question from press about Ares I, whether it should be "killed'. #hsfreport
Augustine - NASA Administrator needs to have the latitude to tailor facilities, structures of centers, workforce. #hsfreport
Augustine - speaking to commercialization, "rather than [NASA] running a trucking service to low-earth orbit." #hsfreport
Augustine - speaking to heavy-lift capability and it being the gateway to getting beyond low-earth orbit. #nasahsf
We suggest your read the ENTIRE report. This is your organization. Stay informed.
Augustine - believe a very strong technology program needed #hsfreport
Important to provide additional funds for utilization of the ISS if it is to be extended. #hsfreport
Ares I issue - whether it's useful, when it has succeeded. Discussing time schedule and cost. Augustine speaking about ISS de-orbit.
Augustine discussing findings. The current program is on an unsustainable trajectory. Mismatch of funding #hsfreport

The committee's task was to list options. Augustine pointing out pros and cons.
Augustine saying there are 5 options outlined. Making it clear he feels heavy lift capability is necessary.
Differences between Ares V and Ares V lite being described by Augustine. #nasahsf
RT @genejm29: #SenateSciComte #HSF Augustine - Almost impossible to manage a program that goes out to 2030 w/unstable funding sources.
Budget is again the topic. Nelson asking Augustine about stability of funding and its possible impact.
Augustine, "I never cease to be amazed...of the commitment of the people." #nasahsf
"Launch fever" brought up again by Augustine. Problem is the budget, "we need to fix that for them." #nasahsf
Flexible Path RT @SarahLena: @NASA_HSF Option 5 was which one again?
"Committee has not discussed personal preference." Augustine- goes briefly over 3, 4, 5. Emphasis on 5. #nasahsf
Nelson, "Do you have a preference on the architecture?" asking Augustine.
Nelson and Augustine discussing Option 3. #nasahsf
Augustine saying the gap is based, good or bad, on decisions made in the past. #nasahsf
Senator Nelson asking if the realities of "the gap" are unavoidable. #nasahsf
Augustine saying you'd be able to accelerate Ares V or alternatives to it. Heavy lift capability #nasahsf
Nelson asking "If you had additional resources, what would you do?" Beyond the $3B. #nasahsf
Senator Nelson asking a series of questions around the themes of the report. #nasahsf
Shuttle to close gap continues to be discussed. #nasahsf
So you know, CAIB = Columbia Accident Investigation Board #nasahsf
Only option to close the gap is to continue shuttle Augustine says. Re-certification necessary for safety. #nasahsf
Senator Hutchison speaking now. Constellation and extending shuttle is being discussed. "The Gap" is the topic. #nasahsf
Senator Nelson asking Augustine about tangible benefits. #nasahsf
Augustine preceded his answer with a few caveats, particularly concerning their background and the task given them. #nasahsf
Augustine, "We think the justification has to be an intangible justification." Talking of putting humans on a path to the solar system.
Senator Nelson asking Augustine to state for the record his thoughts on human exploration being worth it.

Augustine speaking to gravity wells. #nasahsf
Option 5, Flexible path, "We tried to define a program that has intermediate milestones." Public and engineers would benefit from these.
"There is some homework that has to be done on the way to Mars." - Augustine, referring to affect on humans and operational unknowns.
Augustine speaking to cost offsets. Space shuttle program brought up. #nasahsf
